        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:52PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Agate Fossil Beds National Monument, or 22 miles
northeast of Torrington, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Scotts Bluff and southern Sioux Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
